questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application deployed on Tomcat experiences a gradual memory leak, eventually leading to an `OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space`. Profiling indicates that millions of `byte[]` arrays are retained. A senior developer points you to the following service bean:

java
@Service
public class ReportService {
    private static final ThreadLocal<byte[]> localBuffer = ThreadLocal.withInitial(() -> new byte[1024 * 1024]); // 1MB

    @Transactional
    public void generateReport(ReportData data) {
        byte[] buffer = localBuffer.get();
        prepareData(data, buffer);
        writeToDatabase(buffer);
        // Business logic continues...
    }
}
